);

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

The differential equation for \(Q\) is 
\[ 
  \frac{dQ}{dt} = r - k Q,
\]
so that 
\[
  \int\frac{dQ}{r - k Q} = \int \, dt,
\]
and, after solving,
\[
  Q = \frac{r}{k} + A e^{-k t}.
\]
When \(t=0\), \(Q=0\), 
\[
  Q = \frac{r}{k} ( 1-e^{-k t}).
\]
Thus,
\[
  Q_{\infty} = \lim_{t \to \infty} Q = \frac{r}{k}.
\]
This is shown in the following graph.
